<div id="wikihead"><h2><a href="http://rephial.org/wiki/UserManual">UserManual</a> &gt; ClassModifiers</h2></div>

<div id="wikicontent"><div class="page"><h3 id="s1_1">Vital statistics:</h3><table border="1"><tr><th></th><th>STR</th><th>INT</th><th>WIS</th><th>DEX</th><th>CON</th><th>CHR</th><th>HD (bonus)</th><th>XP/level</th></tr><tr><td>Warrior</td><td>+5</td><td>-2</td><td>-2</td><td>+2</td><td>+2</td><td>-1</td><td>9</td><td>+0%</td></tr><tr><td>Mage</td><td>-5</td><td>+3</td><td>0</td><td>+1</td><td>-2</td><td>+1</td><td>0</td><td>+30%</td></tr><tr><td>Priest</td><td>-1</td><td>-3</td><td>+3</td><td>-1</td><td>0</td><td>+2</td><td>2</td><td>+20%</td></tr><tr><td>Rogue</td><td>+2</td><td>+1</td><td>-2</td><td>+3</td><td>+1</td><td>-1</td><td>6</td><td>+25%</td></tr><tr><td>Ranger</td><td>+2</td><td>+2</td><td>0</td><td>+1</td><td>+1</td><td>+1</td><td>4</td><td>+30%</td></tr><tr><td>Paladin</td><td>+3</td><td>-3</td><td>+1</td><td>0</td><td>+2</td><td>+2</td><td>6</td><td>+35%</td></tr></table><p>To get the total hit dice and experience modifier, add the race and class numbers together. For example: A Dwarven Priest has a hit die of 11 + 2 = 13, so will get 1d13 extra hit points per level before constitution bonuses. He has an experience modifier of 20% + 20% = 40%, so will take 40% more experience to advance than a human warrior.<h3 id="s1_2">Abilities:</h3><table border="1"><tr><th rowspan="2">Class</th><th colspan="2">disarm</th><th colspan="2">device</th><th colspan="2">save</th><th rowspan="2">stealth</th><th rowspan="2">search</th><th rowspan="2">percep</th><th colspan="2">melee</th><th colspan="2">missile</th></tr><tr><td>L1</td><td>L50</td><td>L1</td><td>L50</td><td>L1</td><td>L50</td><td>L1</td><td>L50</td><td>L1</td><td>L50</td></tr><tr><td>Warrior</td><td>56</td><td>66</td><td>50</td><td>54</td><td>56</td><td>82</td><td>1</td><td>14</td><td>2</td><td>100</td><td>100</td><td>76</td><td>99</td></tr><tr><td>Mage</td><td>67</td><td>48</td><td>100</td><td>100</td><td>94</td><td>76</td><td>2</td><td>16</td><td>20</td><td>49</td><td>34</td><td>28</td><td>33</td></tr><tr><td>Priest</td><td>56</td><td>47</td><td>83</td><td>77</td><td>100</td><td>100</td><td>2</td><td>16</td><td>8</td><td>69</td><td>45</td><td>49</td><td>45</td></tr><tr><td>Rogue</td><td>100</td><td>100</td><td>89</td><td>78</td><td>88</td><td>84</td><td>5</td><td>32</td><td>24</td><td>86</td><td>89</td><td>92</td><td>67</td></tr><tr><td>Ranger</td><td>67</td><td>54</td><td>89</td><td>78</td><td>88</td><td>84</td><td>3</td><td>24</td><td>16</td><td>80</td><td>67</td><td>100</td><td>100</td></tr><tr><td>Paladin</td><td>44</td><td>47</td><td>67</td><td>76</td><td>78</td><td>91</td><td>1</td><td>12</td><td>2</td><td>97</td><td>78</td><td>56</td><td>66</td></tr></table><p>Values for disarm, device, save, melee, and missile are percentile rankings relative to the other classes, and are given at levels 1 and 50. Values for stealth, search, and perception are absolute skill values, and do not change with level. Note that prayers and spells can improve many of these skills dramatically.<p>Warriors become resistant to fear at level 30.<p>Rangers get a second shot per turn with bows at level 20, and a third at level 40.<h3 id="s1_3">Melee blows:</h3><table border="1"><tr><th></th><th>Max Blows</th><th>Min Weapon Weight</th><th>Weapon Speed Modifier</th></tr><tr><td>Warrior</td><td>6</td><td>3.0</td><td>0.5</td></tr><tr><td>Mage</td><td>4</td><td>4.0</td><td>0.2</td></tr><tr><td>Priest</td><td>4</td><td>3.5</td><td>0.3</td></tr><tr><td>Rogue</td><td>5</td><td>3.0</td><td>0.4</td></tr><tr><td>Ranger</td><td>5</td><td>3.5</td><td>0.4</td></tr><tr><td>Paladin</td><td>5</td><td>3.0</td><td>0.5</td></tr></table><p>All classes can get multiple melee blows per round. To calculate how many blows a character will receive, follow these steps:<ol type="1"><li>Get the character&#39;s Adjusted Strength for Blows (ASB) from the ASB table below. ASB equals Strength if STR is 17 or less.<li>Divide the ASB by the weight of the wielded weapon in pounds, or the class&#39;s Min Weapon Weight (MWW), whichever is higher.<li>Multiply the result by the class&#39;s Weapon Speed Modifer (WSM).<li>Round the result down to obtain the Strength Weapon Index (SWI).<li>The number of blows is the class&#39;s Max Blows, or the number from the blows table corresponding to the SWI and the character&#39;s Dexterity score, whichever is lower.</ol><h4 id="s2_1">ASB Table:</h4><table border="1"><tr><th>Strength</th><th>ASB</th><th>Strength</th><th>ASB</th><th>Strength</th><th>ASB</th></tr><tr><td align="right">3 - 17</td><td>*</td><td align="right">18/70 - 18/79</td><td>90</td><td align="right">18/150 - 18/159</td><td>170</td></tr><tr><td align="right">18 - 18/09</td><td>20</td><td align="right">18/80 - 18/89</td><td>100</td><td align="right">18/160 - 18/169</td><td>180</td></tr><tr><td align="right">18/10 - 18/19</td><td>30</td><td align="right">18/90 - 18/99</td><td>110</td><td align="right">18/170 - 18/179</td><td>190</td></tr><tr><td align="right">18/20 - 18/29</td><td>40</td><td align="right">18/100 - 18/109</td><td>120</td><td align="right">18/180 - 18/189</td><td>200</td></tr><tr><td align="right">18/30 - 18/39</td><td>50</td><td align="right">18/110 - 18/119</td><td>130</td><td align="right">18/190 - 18/199</td><td>210</td></tr><tr><td align="right">18/40 - 18/49</td><td>60</td><td align="right">18/120 - 18/129</td><td>140</td><td align="right">18/200 - 18/209</td><td>220</td></tr><tr><td align="right">18/50 - 18/59</td><td>70</td><td align="right">18/130 - 18/139</td><td>150</td><td align="right">18/210 - 18/219</td><td>230</td></tr><tr><td align="right">18/60 - 18/69</td><td>80</td><td align="right">18/140 - 18/149</td><td>160</td><td align="right">18/220+</td><td>240</td></tr></table><h4 id="s2_2">Blows Table:</h4><table border="1"><tr><th rowspan="2">Dexterity</th><th colspan="12">Strength-Weapon Index (SWI)</th></tr><tr><td align="right">0</td><td>1</td><td>2</td><td>3</td><td>4</td><td>5</td><td>6</td><td>7</td><td>8</td><td>9</td><td>10</td><td>11+</td></tr><tr><td align="right">3 - 9</td><td>1</td><td>1</td><td>1</td><td>1</td><td>1</td><td>2</td><td>2</td><td>2</td><td>3</td><td>3</td><td>3</td><td>3</td></tr><tr><td align="right">10 - 18/09</td><td>1</td><td>1</td><td>1</td><td>2</td><td>2</td><td>2</td><td>2</td><td>3</td><td>3</td><td>3</td><td>3</td><td>3</td></tr><tr><td align="right">18/10 - 18/49</td><td>1</td><td>1</td><td>2</td><td>2</td><td>2</td><td>3</td><td>3</td><td>3</td><td>3</td><td>4</td><td>4</td><td>4</td></tr><tr><td align="right">18/50 - 18/69</td><td>1</td><td>1</td><td>2</td><td>3</td><td>3</td><td>3</td><td>3</td><td>4</td><td>4</td><td>4</td><td>4</td><td>4</td></tr><tr><td align="right">18/70 - 18/89</td><td>1</td><td>2</td><td>3</td><td>3</td><td>3</td><td>4</td><td>4</td><td>4</td><td>4</td><td>4</td><td>4</td><td>4</td></tr><tr><td align="right">18/90 - 18/99</td><td>1</td><td>2</td><td>3</td><td>4</td><td>4</td><td>4</td><td>4</td><td>4</td><td>4</td><td>4</td><td>4</td><td>4</td></tr><tr><td align="right">18/100 - 18/109</td><td>2</td><td>3</td><td>4</td><td>4</td><td>4</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td></tr><tr><td align="right">18/110 - 18/119</td><td>2</td><td>3</td><td>4</td><td>4</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td></tr><tr><td align="right">18/120 - 18/129</td><td>2</td><td>3</td><td>4</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>6</td></tr><tr><td align="right">18/130 - 18/139</td><td>2</td><td>4</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>6</td><td>6</td></tr><tr><td align="right">18/140 - 18/149</td><td>2</td><td>4</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>6</td><td>6</td><td>6</td><td>6</td></tr><tr><td align="right">18/150+</td><td>3</td><td>4</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>5</td><td>6</td><td>6</td><td>6</td><td>6</td><td>6</td><td>6</td><td>6</td></tr></table></div></div>

